100% of the doctors and patients reported overall improvement in the treatment due to better quality of scans;
53% of the patients seeking financial aid from hospitals supported by ICS were funded by ICICI Foundation;
Majority of the patients that received funds for cancer treatment were from low-income background, underscoring the relevance of the financial assistance.
There was a 25% reduction in scan time, increasing the capability of the hospital to take more scans. About 80,000 patients are estimated to benefit from the upgrade during the lifespan of the equipment;
An increase in revenue of ` 3.5 lakh was reported by the hospital from the use of the upgraded equipment between July 2023 to March 2024, and which was being utilized for providing subsidized treatment to underprivileged patients.
